  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Invert Binary Tree\n\nMirror a binary tree by swapping the left and right child of every node, then return the root.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: root = [4,2,7,1,3,6,9]\nOutput: [4,7,2,9,6,3,1]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: root = [2,1,3]\nOutput: [2,3,1]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: root = []\nOutput: []\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- The judge provides a `TreeNode` class with `val`, `left`, and `right` fields.\n- Trees are shown in level-order form with `null` for missing children.\n- Node counts are sized for local offline execution.",
  "editorial": "Recursively swap children after inverting each subtree, or perform the same swaps with a queue.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def invertTree(self, root):\n        if not root:\n            return None\n        root.left, root.right = self.invertTree(root.right), self.invertTree(root.left)\n        return root\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Every node can be handled independently.",
    "The root value never changes."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def invertTree(self, root):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
    "class_name": "Solution",
    "method_name": "invertTree"
  },
  "checker": {
    "type": "exact"
  },
  "time_limit_ms": 2000,
  "memory_limit_mb": 256,
